# tvOS Design Rules — Apple TV

**Project context:** Pair with [.cursor/rules/tvos-safari-design-language.mdc](tvos-safari-design-language.mdc) for TV Safari browser chrome and `BrowserLayout`. See [.cursor/rules/apple-hig-design-governance.mdc](apple-hig-design-governance.mdc) for shared principles. **Launch UI:** use `LaunchScreen.storyboard` + imageset (`LESSONS_LEARNED.md` §31), not deprecated `LaunchImage.launchimage`.

## The 10-Foot Experience

ALL design decisions start from this fact: users sit ~10 feet (3 meters) from the screen.

### Layout

- Screen resolution: **1920×1080** at 1x scale.
- Use grid-based layouts. Rows and columns with horizontal scrolling.
- **40pt** minimum horizontal spacing between grid items.
- ALL UI elements must be larger than iOS equivalents — buttons, controls, text, images.
- Generous spacing between elements. Items must be individually distinguishable from distance.
- Respect system safe areas. Content near edges gets clipped by TV bezels.
- When content extends beyond screen edge, show **10–20%** of the next item to signal scrollability.

### Typography

- System font: **SF Pro**. Auto-selects Display (≥40pt) / Text (≤39pt).
- Body text minimum: ~**29pt**. NEVER go below **18pt** for any visible text.
- Use heavier font weights. Bold and semibold preferred for distance readability.
- Minimize on-screen text. People don't read paragraphs on television.
- Custom fonts: must use heavy weights AND support accessibility features.

> Source: WWDC 2016 Session 802 — "Don't be afraid to go big and bold with text on TV."  
> Source: Apple HIG — Foundations > Typography

### Color & Theming

- Support light AND dark appearances (tvOS room-lighting-based switching).
- High-contrast visuals mandatory. Test readability from across the room.
- Use system colors as defaults — they adapt automatically.

## Focus-Based Navigation

tvOS does NOT use touch. Users navigate via the Siri Remote focus engine.

### Focus Rules

- The focused element must be **immediately obvious** at a glance.
- Focused items: elevate, scale up, add shadow. System provides this for standard components.
- Focus movement must be **predictable**. Swipe direction = focus direction. No skipping, no ambiguity.
- Never break the focus engine. Use system focus behaviors.
- All interactive elements MUST be reachable via focus navigation.

### Focus States (required for every focusable element)

1. **Unfocused** — default resting state  
2. **Focused** — elevated, scaled, shadowed  
3. **Pressed** — depressed/highlighted on click  
4. **Disabled** — 0.3–0.4 alpha opacity  

### Parallax Effect

- **MANDATORY** for app icons (2–5 layers).
- **STRONGLY RECOMMENDED** for all focusable image-based content.
- Foreground layers: prominent elements (characters, text, logos).
- Middle layers: secondary content, shadow effects.
- Background layers: opaque backdrops. MUST be fully opaque.
- Text goes on the **FRONT** layer so parallax tilt doesn't obscure it.
- Maintain ~**5%** safe zone inset — layers scale/shift during parallax.

## Siri Remote Input Model

| Input | Behavior | Use For |
|-------|----------|---------|
| **Swipe** | Moves focus directionally. Starts fast, decelerates. | Navigating between items |
| **Tap** | Navigates one-by-one through collections. Region-specific direction. | Precise single-step navigation |
| **Click** | Activates/selects the focused item. | Confirming actions |
| **Click+Hold** | Context-specific secondary action (e.g. edit mode). | Contextual menus |
| **MENU** | Navigate back. At top level → Home screen. | **Do not** break this contract in system-reserved ways. |
| **HOME** | Return to tvOS home screen. | **Never** intercept. |
| **Play/Pause** | Start media playback or skip cutscenes. | Media control |

### Input Safety

Users rest thumbs on the touch surface, pick up/replace remote, hand to others. Design interactions that tolerate incidental touch.

## App Icons

tvOS icons are **LAYERED** for parallax.

```
Layer 1 (Back)   — Fully opaque background. NO transparency.
Layer 2 (Mid)    — Secondary effects, atmosphere, shadows.
Layer 3 (Front)  — Primary glyph, logo, focal element.
```

### Icon Rules

- Single centered focus point. One visual element, centered.
- NO text on the icon. System renders app name below.
- Fill the entire canvas edge-to-edge.
- Background layer MUST be fully opaque.
- Safe zone: ~5% inset from edges for parallax cropping.

### Required Sizes

| Context | Dimensions | Layers |
|---------|-----------|--------|
| Home Screen @1x | 400×240 | 2–5 PNG layers |
| Home Screen @2x | 800×480 | 2–5 PNG layers |
| App Store | 1280×768 | 2–5 PNG layers |

## Top Shelf

### Required Assets

| Type | Size | Notes |
|------|------|-------|
| Standard | 1920×720 | Required for all apps |
| Wide | 2320×720 | Required since tvOS 10 |

### Top Shelf Rules

- At minimum: one static image. Required for App Store submission.
- Dynamic content strongly recommended: recent, personalized, or featured items.
- NEVER show advertisements.
- Purchasable content OK but NEVER display prices.
- Deep-link every Top Shelf item directly into relevant app content.
- Use layered images for parallax where possible.

## Navigation Components

### Tab Bar

- Primary top-level navigation. Sits at screen top; fully visible only when focused.
- ALL tabs must fit on screen at once. No scrolling tab bars.
- Each tab provides clear value. No junk drawers.
- App Settings → put in System Settings, not in the tab bar.

### Alerts

- Maximum 2 buttons preferred.
- Destructive actions: red label + confirmation step.
- MENU button dismisses alerts.

### Text Input

- MINIMIZE text entry. tvOS keyboard is cumbersome.
- Always provide placeholder text.
- Show recent searches before user starts typing.
- Use appropriate keyboard types (email, URL, numeric).
- Support physical keyboard connection.

## Code Patterns

### SwiftUI Focus (tvOS)

```swift
@FocusState private var focusedItem: String?

Button("Action") { }
    .focused($focusedItem, equals: "action")

.onMoveCommand { direction in
    switch direction {
    case .left: break
    case .right: break
    default: break
    }
}
```

### Accessibility Compliance

```swift
Image("poster")
    .accessibilityLabel("Movie Title: Example")
    .accessibilityHint("Select to play")

@Environment(\.accessibilityReduceMotion) var reduceMotion
.animation(reduceMotion ? nil : .easeInOut, value: isFocused)
```

> Apple HIG — Designing for tvOS: https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/designing-for-tvos
